	  <concept id="i1081348"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">32.908</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d2158e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2172e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1050233.dita#i1050233"
                        base="i1050233"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.232-26</xref>, Prompt Payment for Fixed-Price Architect-Engineer Contracts, in solicitations and contracts that contain the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1049582.dita#i1049582"
                        base="i1049582"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.232-10</xref>, Payments Under Fixed-Price Architect-Engineer Contracts.</p>
					          <ol id="d2158e29" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e33" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                As authorized in <xref href="FAR-i1081142.dita#i1081142"
                              base="i1081142"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">32.904</xref>(c)(2), the contracting officer may modify the date in paragraph (a)(4)(i) of the clause to specify a period longer than 7 days for constructive acceptance or constructive approval, if required to afford the Government a practicable opportunity to inspect and test the supplies furnished or evaluate the services performed.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e45" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                As provided in <xref href="FAR-i1081128.dita#i1081128"
                              base="i1081128"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">32.903</xref>, agency policies and procedures may authorize amendment of paragraphs(a)(1)(i) and (ii) of the clause to insert a period shorter than 30 days (but not less than 7 days) for making contract invoice payments.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2172e59" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1050318.dita#i1050318"
                        base="i1050318"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.232-27</xref>, Prompt Payment for Construction Contracts, in all solicitations and contracts for construction (see <xref href="FAR-i1079251.dita#i1079251"
                        base="i1079251"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  36</xref>).</p>
					          <ol id="d2158e71" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e75" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                As authorized in <xref href="FAR-i1081142.dita#i1081142"
                              base="i1081142"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">32.904</xref>(d)(1)(i)(B), the contracting officer may modify the date in paragraph (a)(1)(i)(A) of the clause to specify a period longer than 14 days if required to afford the Government a reasonable opportunity to adequately inspect the work and to determine the adequacy of the Contractor’s performance under the contract.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e87" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                As authorized in <xref href="FAR-i1081142.dita#i1081142"
                              base="i1081142"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">32.904</xref>(d)(2)(iv), the contracting officer may modify the date in paragraph (a)(4)(i) of the clause to specify a period longer than 7 days for constructive acceptance or constructive approval if required to afford the Government a reasonable opportunity to inspect and test the supplies furnished or evaluate the services performed.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d2172e101" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1050125.dita#i1050125"
                        base="i1050125"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.232-25</xref>, Prompt Payment, in all other solicitations and contracts, except when the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1060971.dita#i1060971"
                        base="i1060971"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.212-4</xref>, Contract Terms and Conditions-Commercial Items, applies, or when payment terms and late payment penalties are established by other governmental authority (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i>tariffs).</p>
					          <ol id="d2158e116" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e120" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                As authorized in <xref href="FAR-i1081142.dita#i1081142"
                              base="i1081142"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">32.904</xref>(b)(1)(ii)(B)(4), the contracting officer may modify the date in paragraph (a)(5)(i) of the clause to specify a period longer than 7 days for constructive acceptance, if required to afford the Government a reasonable opportunity to inspect and test the supplies furnished or to evaluate the services performed, except in the case of a contract for the purchase of a commercial item, including a brand-name commercial item for authorized resale (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i>commissary items).</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e135" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                As provided in <xref href="FAR-i1081128.dita#i1081128"
                              base="i1081128"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">32.903</xref>, agency policies and procedures may authorize amendment of paragraphs(a)(1)(i) and (ii) of the clause to insert a period shorter than 30 days (but not less than 7 days) for making contract invoice payments.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d2172e147" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                If the contract is a cost-reimbursement contract for services, use the clause with its AlternateI.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
